<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                    <head>No. 47.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Logan</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-04-02"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 2,
                            1883</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Logan is informed that the action of Mr. Partridge, as reported by Mr.
                        Logan, is unauthorized, and that he has been directed to make explanations;
                        that instructions suggesting the recognition of the government of Calderon
                        have been sent by mail.</p>
                    <p>Tarapaca to be ceded to Chili by Peru. United States will agree to arbitrate
                        in the event that Chili is to receive any further indemnity.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>